subject: p14147787
Findings: PA and lateral upright chest radiographs were reviewed in comparison to and multiple prior studies dating back to. Bilateral upper lungs lateral opacties appear similar in distribution, stable since most recent radiograph but overall decreased in the intensity as compared to remote studies, consistent with known history of sarcoidosis. There are no new consolidations, masses, or interstitial abnormality seen. There is no pleural effusion or pneumothorax.
